Vendored third-party browser bundle
===================================

app-with-deps.js
----------------
MCP Apps client SDK (the `App` class plus its bundled dependencies), used by
src/sqllens/ui/query_results.html to talk to an apps-aware MCP host over the
postMessage JSON-RPC channel defined by the MCP Apps spec (2026-01-26).

Source : https://www.npmjs.com/package/@modelcontextprotocol/ext-apps
Package: @modelcontextprotocol/ext-apps@1.7.2
Path    : dist/src/app-with-deps.js
URL     : https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@modelcontextprotocol/ext-apps@1.7.2/dist/src/app-with-deps.js
sha256  : e72bf921bc15d38951cf85abbb8e572688a30572db89b5344e3a447b1f8d6b40
bytes   : 337227
license : MIT (the @modelcontextprotocol/ext-apps project)

It is an ES module (it ends with `export { ... as App }`); the widget imports
it with `<script type="module">` from this same origin. There is no Node build
pipeline, no package.json, and no node_modules — upgrading is a manual
file-drop: re-download the URL above for the new version, replace this file,
and update the version / URL / sha256 / bytes lines here.

echarts.min.js
--------------
Apache ECharts (minified UMD build), used by
src/sqllens/ui/chart_results.html to render the chart widget. Loaded as a
classic same-origin <script> tag (it is UMD, not an ES module) so the global
`echarts` is available to the widget's module script. No CDN, no fonts, no
remote requests.

Source : https://www.npmjs.com/package/echarts
Package: echarts@5.5.1
Path    : dist/echarts.min.js
URL     : https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/echarts@5.5.1/dist/echarts.min.js
sha256  : e84270bd0cd5bdf60fefc26d00c2a391cb2e81f4d26a7a9ee16185a54773a3cf
bytes   : 1030855
license : Apache-2.0 (the Apache ECharts project)

Upgrading is the same manual file-drop as above: re-download the URL for the
new version, replace this file, and update the version / URL / sha256 / bytes
lines here.

To verify the committed copies match the recorded hashes:

    sha256sum src/sqllens/ui/vendor/app-with-deps.js
    sha256sum src/sqllens/ui/vendor/echarts.min.js
